Green electricity generation in Scotland has increased by nearly a third thanks to the growth of hydro and wind power. Green power is go as generation jumps by 30% Green electricity generation in Scotland has increased by nearly a third thanks to the growth of hydro and wind power.The amount of electricity produced from renewable sources in the first half of 2014 was 30% higher than in the same period last year, according to new figures from the UK Department of Energy and Climate Change.Hydro generation increased by half, while wind output rose 20%.Renewables are estimated to have provided 46% of gross electricity consumption in 2013, up from 40% the year before. 